The Filesystem Hierarchy Standard (FHS) defines the directory structure and directory contents in Linux distributions.
To compile software package, Iâ€™ll need to download the source code
afer download completed, i go to store and unpack:
  cd source
  tar xzvf example.tar.gz
  cd example
then, reading Document. The documentation may point me to other software that i need to install before i can install this package
  less INSTALL
after that, building
  ./configure
compile
  make
  make install
  
To manage package compile, i will use VCS tool
